 in Albany  GA from 1988 to 2000  His next assignment  in Pensacola  FL  increased his responsibilities to include recruiting enlisted and OTS applicants to include technical  non technical  pilot and navigator programs  In 2003 Mr  Douglass was promoted and transferred to Raleigh  NC where he recruited for the Air Force s Medical Corps  MC  Nurse Corps  NC  Biomedical Services Corps  BSC  and the Medical Services Corps  MSC  In April 2008 Mr  Douglass was transferred to Boise  ID where he served in a supervisory position as the Senior Air Force Liaison at the Boise Military Enlistment Processing Station  MEPS  Mr  Douglass was transferred in 2000 to the Air Force Recruiting School as an instructor for newly assigned recruiters  Through a humanitarian reassignment he was transferred back home to attend to his family and conclude his career as the Air Force Liaison at the Raleigh MEPS  Mr  Douglass retired from the Air Force in 2003 as a Master Sergeant  His initial career after retirement was with Johnson   Johnson as a Pharmaceutical Sales Representative in Roanoke  VA  2003   2010  He left the pharmaceutical industry in 2010 to recruit for Nashville Auto Diesel College  NADC  where he was able to return to his passion of assisting students in continuing their education  Mr  Douglass has been at VMI since January 2015  Education Business Administration in Management   Organizational Leadership  George Fox University  Associate Degree in Air Traffic Control Management  Community College of The Air Force  Personal Mr  Douglass is married to Judy Douglass and they have 2 daughters  Morgan   Shannon  and a son  Sean  Mr  Douglass  passion is in volunteering and watching his children develop their talents in travel soccer  travel volleyball and recreation basketball  baseball and football  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 